br> BlueEFFICIENCY\n|2011\u20132014\n|[[Mercedes-Benz OM642|OM642 DE30]] <br> 3.0&nbsp;L [[V6 engine|V6]] [[turbocharger|turbo]]\n|{{convert|195|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} <br> @ 3,800 rpm\n|{{convert|620|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} <br> @ 1,600\u20132,400 rpm\n|6.2 s\n|-\n|CLS350 <br> BlueTEC\n|2014\u20132017\n|[[Mercedes-Benz OM642|OM642 LS DE30]] <br> 3.0&nbsp;L [[V6 engine|V6]] [[turbocharger|turbo]]\n|{{convert|190|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} <br> @ 3,400 rpm\n|{{convert|620|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} <br> @ 1,600\u20132,400 rpm\n|6.5 s\n|}\n\n== CLS63 AMG ==\n{{main|Mercedes-Benz CLS63 AMG}}\n[[File:Mercedes Benz CLS 63 AMG 4Matic 2013.jpg|thumb|CLS63 AMG sedan]]\n[[File:Mercedes-Benz CLS63 AMG (C218) rear.JPG|thumb|CLS63 AMG sedan]]\nThe CLS63 AMG is a high performance variant of the CLS and went on sale on March 2011.<ref>[http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-1346972-1-1347119-1-0-0-0-0-1-11701-854934-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html AMG V8 biturbo engine consuming 9.9 litres per 100 km: CLS 63 AMG \u2013 the benchmark in design, performance and efficiency]</ref> It features a 5.5 L twin-turbo V8 rated at {{convert|386|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|700|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.autoexpress.co.uk/mercedes/cls-class/63-amg|title=Mercedes CLS 63 AMG (2011-2017) Review|work=Auto Express|access-date=31 May 2018|language=en}}</ref> Standard equipment includes an [[Mercedes-Benz 7G-Tronic transmission#AMG SpeedShift MCT|AMG SPEEDSHIFT MCT 7-speed transmission]], a {{convert|24|mm|in|0|abbr=on}} wider front [[axle track|track]], larger 360 mm ventilated and perforated brake discs, an AMG sports exhaust system, and a three-spoke AMG Performance steering wheel with shift paddles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnet.com/roadshow/auto/2013-mercedes-benz-cls-class/review/|title=Effortlessly fast AMG saddled with slow tech|date=5 June 2013|work=Roadshow|access-date=31 May 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://gtspirit.com/2013/04/22/first-drive-mercedes-benz-cls-63-amg/|title=First Drive: Mercedes-Benz CLS 63 AMG - GTspirit|last=Adams|first=Lawrence|date=22 April 2013|work=GTspirit|access-date=31 May 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> The CLS63 AMG is available in both sedan and Shooting Brake variants, as well as in rear-wheel drive or all-wheel drive 4MATIC configurations.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://autoweek.com/article/car-reviews/2014-mercedes-benz-cls63-amg-s-model-4matic-review-notes|title=2014 Mercedes-Benz CLS63 AMG S-Model 4Matic review notes|work=Autoweek|access-date=31 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nEdition 1 models were available exclusively in the first year of its market launch, and featured minor power increases of {{convert|29|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|100|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.topgear.com/car-news/merc-reveals-cls63-amg-shooting-brake|title=Merc reveals CLS63 AMG Shooting Brake|date=9 July 2012|work=Top Gear|access-date=31 May 2018|language=en}}</ref> Other additions include Edition 1 insignia, matte exterior paintwork, designo leather, and a choice of three AMG exclusive interior trim.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.topspeed.com/cars/mercedes/2013-mercedes-cls-63-amg-shooting-brake-ar118307.html|title=2013 Mercedes CLS 63 AMG Shooting Brake Review @ Top Speed|work=Top Speed|access-date=31 May 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> An AMG Performance Package was also offered separately, and featured a carbon-fibre spoiler lip, red brake calipers,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/motoring/car-manufacturers/mercedes-benz/8516454/Mercedes-Benz-CLS-63-AMG-review.html|title=Mercedes-Benz CLS 63 AMG review|last=English|first=Andrew|date=6 June 2011|access-date=31 May 2018|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235}}</ref> and increased performance gains of {{convert|24|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|100|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}, resulting in a 0-60 mph time of 4.1 s.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.caranddriver.com/news/2012-mercedes-benz-cls63-amg-mercedes-benz-cls-news|title=2012 Mercedes-Benz CLS63 AMG|work=Car and Driver|access-date=31 May 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n\nFrom April 2013, the CLS63 AMG range was updated to now produce {{convert|410|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|720|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.carmagazine.co.uk/car-news/first-official-pictures/mercedes-benz/mercedes-cls63-amg-gets-more-power-for-2013/|title=Mercedes CLS63 AMG gets more power for 2013|work=CAR Magazine|access-date=31 May 2018|language=en}}</ref> The Performance Package was also replaced by the new CLS63 AMG S model,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.topspeed.com/cars/mercedes/2014-mercedes-cls-63-amg-4matic-ar158131.html|title=2014 Mercedes CLS 63 AMG 4MATIC Review @ Top Speed|work=Top Speed|access-date=31 May 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> featuring further performance and efficiency enhancements, all-wheel drive 4MATIC as standard, and a rear [[locking differential]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.evo.co.uk/mercedes/cls/7369/mercedes-cls63-amg-s-review-price-and-specs|title=Mercedes CLS63 AMG S review, price and specs|work=Evo|access-date=31 May 2018|language=en}}</ref> It is also available as a Shooting Brake variant and launched in June 2013.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://media.daimler.com/marsMediaSite/en/instance/ko.xhtml?oid=9918572&ls=L3NlYXJjaHJlc3VsdC9zZWFyY2hyZXN1bHQueGh0bWw_c2VhcmNoU3RyaW5nPUNMUyZzZWFyY2hJZD0wJnNlYXJjaFR5cGU9ZGV0YWlsZWQmYm9yZGVycz10cnVlJnJlc3VsdEluZm9UeXBlSWQ9NDA2MjYmdmlld1R5cGU9bGlzdCZzb3J0RGVmaW5pdGlvbj1QVUJMSVNIRURfQVQtMiZ0aHVtYlNjYWxlSW5kZXg9MCZyb3dDb3VudHNJbmRleD01&rs=24|title=Mercedes-Benz CLS 63 AMG: performance, dynamism and efficiency - The new benchmark: CLS 63 AMG as S-Model and with 4MATIC {{!}} marsMediaSite|website=marsMediaSite|language=en-EN|access-date=31 May 2018}}</ref>\n{{clear right}}\n\n== Model year changes ==\n{{Multiple image\n| align = right\n| direction = vertical\n| width = \n| image1 = Mercedes-Benz CLS 350d 2987cc registererd January 2016.jpg\n| caption1 = \n| image2 = 2015 Mercedes-Benz CLS550 interior.jpg\n| caption2 = Facelift W218 CLS sedan\n}}\n\n=== 2014 facelift ===\nA [[facelift (automotive)|facelift]] was introduced for the CLS model range in 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autocar.co.uk/car-news/goodwood-festival-speed/facelifted-mercedes-benz-cls-and-cls-shooting-brake-revealed|title=Facelifted Mercedes-Benz CLS and CLS Shooting Brake revealed {{!}} Autocar|website=www.autocar.co.uk|language=en|access-date=31 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe major changes are:\n\n* A redesigned front fascia with a diamond-patterned radiator grille and new anti-dazzle MULTIBEAM LED headlights<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.carmagazine.co.uk/car-news/first-official-pictures/mercedes-benz/mercedes-cls-facelift-2014-first-official-pics-/|title=Mercedes CLS facelift (2014) first official pics|work=CAR Magazine|access-date=31 May 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/cars/mercedes-benz/mercedes-cls-review/|title=Mercedes CLS review|last=Huntingford|first=Steve|date=9 December 2015|work=The Telegraph|access-date=31 May 2018|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235}}</ref> \n* Interior changes including a new steering wheel design and a larger free standing 8-inch COMAND APS display<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.motortrend.com/cars/mercedes-benz/cls-class/2015/|title=2015 Mercedes-Benz CLS-Class Model Overview|website=MotorTrend|access-date=31 May 2018}}</ref> \n* New model naming scheme for diesel engines (CLS350 CDI BlueEFFICIENCY now called CLS350d)\n* Introduction of CLS400 and CLS220d models, and updated CLS350d engine<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newatlas.com/mercedes-cls-styling-update/32705/|title=Mercedes CLS gets a mid-life facelift|website=newatlas.com|language=en|access-date=31 May 2018}}</ref>\n* Introduction of [[Mercedes-Benz 9G-Tronic transmission|9G-Tronic nine-speed automatic transmission]] on all models (excluding the CLS400)<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.carmagazine.co.uk/car-news/first-official-pictures/mercedes-benz/mercedes-cls-facelift-2014-first-official-pics-/|title=Mercedes CLS facelift (2014) first official pics|work=CAR Magazine|access-date=31 May 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n\n=== 2016 ===\n* CLS400 receives 9-speed automatic transmission\n\n== Sales figures ==\nAs with the previous generation, the CLS sedan and Shooting Brake models are produced in [[Sindelfingen]], [[Germany]].<ref>[http://www.autoblog.com/2010/11/08/mercedes-benz-confirms-production-of-cls-shooting-brake/ Mercedes-Benz confirms production of CLS Shooting Brake]</ref>\n\nThe following are the sales figures for the W218 CLS in Europe '''only''':<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://carsalesbase.com/european-car-sales-data/mercedes-benz/mercedes-benz-cls/|title=Mercedes-Benz CLS European sales figures|work=carsalesbase.com|access-date=28 May 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Year\n!Total\n|-\n|2011\n|17,414\n|-\n|2012\n|12,797\n|-\n|2013\n|15,139\n|-\n|2014\n|10,289\n|-\n|2015\n|12,600\n|-\n|2016\n|7,803\n|-\n|2017\n|5,116\n|-\n|'''Total:'''\n|'''81,158'''\n|}\n\n== Awards ==\n* 2010 [[Auto Bild]] 'Golden Steering Wheel Award'<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.emercedesbenz.com/autos/mercedes-benz/cls-class/mercedes-benz-cls-class-wins-golden-steering-wheel-award/|title=Mercedes-Benz CLS-Class Wins Golden Steering Wheel Award {{!}} eMercedesBenz|last=Davis|first=Jim|access-date=31 May 2018}}</ref>\n* 2010 [[Autozeitung|Auto Zeitung]] 'Best Car of the Year' (luxury segment)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://media.daimler.com/marsMediaSite/en/instance/ko/Mercedes-CLS-and-SLS-AMG-voted-best-cars-of-the-year-Three-awards-in-Auto-Trophy-2010.xhtml?oid=9914976|title=Mercedes CLS and SLS AMG voted best cars of the year: Three awards in Auto Trophy 2010 {{!}} marsMediaSite|website=marsMediaSite|language=en-EN|access-date=31 May 2018}}</ref>\n* 2011 [[auto motor und sport]] 'Autonis Awards'<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.la.mercedes-benz.com/content/latina/mpc/mpc_latina_website/en/home_mpc/passengercars/home/world